{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"title":"Meringue Cloud Cakes","content":["Preheat the oven to 250°F. Line a baking sheet with parchment or a silicone baking mat.","Place sugar into mixing bowl and grind <b>10 sec\/speed 10<b>. Transfer to a bowl and set aside."," <strong>Insert butterfly whisk<\/strong>. Place egg whites and salt into mixing bowl and whip <b>4 min\/105°F\/speed 3.5<b>. Add cream of tartar and without measuring cup whip a further <b>15 min\/105°F\/speed 3.5<b> while adding 1 tbsp reserved ground sugar at a time through hole in mixing bowl lid.","Add cornstarch, vanilla and lemon juice through hole in mixing bowl lid and mix <b>4 sec\/speed 3.5<b>. <strong>Remove butterfly whisk<\/strong>.","On prepared baking sheet, use a spoon to gently form six cloud-like circles of whipped egg mixture directly on parchment. With back of spoon create a small indentation in the center of each.","Bake for 75 minutes (250°F) or until meringues are dry with a creamy color. <strong>Do not open the oven door<\/strong> while meringues are baking to avoid collapsing.","Once done, turn off oven and allow meringues to cool in oven until outsides crack slightly (approx. 2 hrs. or overnight). Meanwhile, clean mixing bowl and make Sabayon Crème."]},{"title":"Sabayon Crème","content":["Place sugar and lemon peel into mixing bowl and grind <b>10 sec\/speed 10<b>."," <strong>Insert butterfly whisk.<\/strong> Add egg yolks and wine and cook <b>9 min\/160°F\/speed 3<b>. <strong>Remove butterfly whisk<\/strong>. Quickly transfer Sabayon Crème to a bowl and set aside to cool."," <strong>Insert butterfly whisk<\/strong>. Place whipping cream into mixing bowl and without setting a time whisk <b>speed 3<b>, until stiff peaks form. <strong>Remove butterfly whisk<\/strong>. Using a large metal spoon, gently fold whipped cream into cooled egg yolk mixture until thoroughly combined.","Top each cooled Meringue Cloud Cake with a ¼ cup fresh berries and ⅓ cup Sabayon Crème. Garnish with fresh basil leaves and serve immediately."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"Meringue Cloud Cakes","content":["8 oz sugar","6 egg whites","1 pinch salt","½ tsp cream of tartar","1 tbsp cornstarch, sifted","½ tsp vanilla extract","2 tsp lemon juice"]},{"title":"Sabayon Crème","content":["3 oz sugar","1 lemon, thin peel only, no pith","4 egg yolks, from large eggs","4 oz white wine (Pinot Grigio)","8 oz heavy whipping cream","1 ½ cups fresh berries, divided","fresh basil leaves, to garnish"]}],"id":"r418412","imageLink":"https:\/\/4.bp.blogspot.com\/-hBeZsz9weiw\/XZWYl1-sVdI\/AAAAAAAAeAg\/ptkpIlid1gIfWbzop0bxNjDAVQFkn1SKQCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_F7Jra73A-P4EVmQK.png","title":"Meringue Clouds with Sabayon and Berries (Rosalyn Darling)","publishedAt":"2019-03-29T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{},"usefulItems":"baking sheet, parchment paper or silicone baking mat, large metal spoon, oven","basicInfo":["medium","45m","4h 50m","6 portions"]}